messages.text: I think my dad is a murderer.
WTF?!
Your dad is innocent.
No he's not.
He already confessed to the accident.
And to drunk driving.
I have a lot of suspicion.
What are you saying?
The way he acts around the house.
Like he's happy your dad is going to prison.
Did he say that?!
No, but I can tell.
It's like he's got some big secret he can't reveal to anyone.
Much more than usual.
My dad was drunk and he hit that car and killed that man.
Now 3 kids have no father. A wife has no husband.
I love him but what he did was wrong, & he accepts his justice.
Why are you trying to interfere?
If you think you're helping, you're not.
This is another election year...
and my dad has been in the Senate since before I was born...
he won't let anything stop him from getting re-elected...
even a fatal car crash.
I'm going now. I can't do this.
Can we speak later?
Jane??
Jane, I'm sorry...
Dad I need to talk.
Can it wait?
No.
Speak to your mother.
No, Dad. It's important.
I think you're hiding something. Something big.
Are you on drugs?
I think you were behind the wheel that night.
Thomas, stop this nonsense.
You were drunk, you hit that car and killed that man.
Where are you getting these ideas?
So it's true?
Of course not.
You're lying... again.
I can't prove it yet. But I will.
You have been under a lot of stress. School, the media, the photos...
Take some time off. I've got an early graduation present for you...
that car you always wanted.
You can't bribe me like I'm one of your campaign donors.
I'm going to the media. Speak out about my suspicions.
Son, if you crawl in that dirt, and roll around with those bottom-feeding maggots...
I will send you to reformatory so fast you won't know what hit you.
That's my promise to you!
Dad you got a minute?
What is it, sweetie
I'm worried about you.
That's so nice. But you know I'll be out in less than 2 years.
and being that it's my first offense
I'll probably get out earlier with good behaviour.
I know, but Tom has been saying some things.
What things?
That you were not the one driving.
That his father was.
That you switched places so his dad could run for re-election.
Tom is just upset. He doesn't know what he is saying.
Give him some time to come around.
He knows his dad pretty well
and I know you very well.
You can't say no to your best friend
even if it means hurting your family.
I know it may be hard to accept that your dad did something very wrong...
but I've always taught you to do the right thing, no matter who it hurts.
What kind of father would I be, what kind of example would I set,
if I didn't do what was right?
You got to understand something:
I'd be more hurt if you were lying
than if you were a serial killer.
You're getting worked up, Jane.
Please get some rest and we'll talk about this another time.
I spoke with my dad.
Thanks. What did he say?
That you've got it wrong. That he was the one driving.
Do u believe that?
I don't know what to believe
I'm going to meet a reporter. Tell him my story.
Tonight.
don't u think u should wait?
u haven't got any evidence
I can't wait and see an innocent man go to jail for something my dad did.
what if ur wrong?
I'm just trying to find the truth.
Be careful.
I will.
And come back soon!
four hours later
Senator, is Tom at home? He doesn't answer his texts.
No, Jane. He said he was going to visit you.
Can you enlighten me as to what's going on?
I have no idea, sir. Please have him call me when he gets home.
Jane, you be careful.
You're a nice girl, and I don't want to see you get hurt by helping Tom in any of his hair-brained ideas.
No, sir.
I'm keeping my eye on you.
five hours later
Any word?
No ma'am. We sent out a patrol, but have not seen Tom.
Jane, why did you call the police?
Answer me.
This is not going to go well for you or for Tom.
You don't know whom you're dealing with!
